# Walkthrough - Shuffled Questions in Pop the Balloon

I have implemented a shuffling mechanism for the "Pop the Balloon" game to ensure that the questions and their internal choices appear in a random order every time the game is played.

## Changes Made

### [poptheballoon.js](file:///d:/CHAD/GRAMMAR%20TREATS%20APRIL%209%20FINALE/Grammar%20Treatsv15.13/games/poptheballoon/poptheballoon.js)

1.  **Added `shuffleArray` Utility**:
    Implemented a Fisher-Yates shuffle function to handle randomization of arrays.
    
    ```javascript
    function shuffleArray(array) {
        for (let i = array.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {
            const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));
            [array[i], array[j]] = [array[j], array[i]];
        }
    }
    ```

2.  **Randomized Questions and Choices**:
    Before the game starts, the `questions` array is now shuffled. Additionally, each question's `choices` array is shuffled to ensure the correct answer is not always on the same balloon.

    ```javascript
    shuffleArray(questions);
    questions.forEach(q => {
        if (q.choices) shuffleArray(q.choices);
    });
    ```

## Verification Results

- **Randomization**: Verified that refreshing the game results in a different starting question and different balloon positions for choices.
- **Game Logic**: Confirmed that the correct answer logic still correctly identifies the right punctuation, even when shuffled.
- **UI Integrity**: The question tracker still correctly displays "Question X of 10".

> [!TIP]
> This change enhances replayability by ensuring players cannot simply memorize the order of answers.
